The paper deals with algorithms for counting triangulations and other non-crossing graphs, which are topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and combinatorics (cs.DM). The use of separators and cactus graphs suggests a connection to graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS, cs.DC), while the application of the framework to various other problems suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC).
